        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 11 at 4:59PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 459 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Parachute, or 35 miles west of Glenwood Springs,
moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of central Garfield
County.

This includes Colorado 13 between mile markers 7 and 15.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
